│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The transformation that relaxes a cttz/ctlz intrinsic to use                  │
│ is_zero_poison=true (i.e., changing the second intrinsic operand to true) is  │
│ performed when the result is used only in a select that guards the zero-input │
│ case. This is usually safe because the poison result is not demanded.         │
│ However, in this reproducer, the call result has the noundef attribute. That  │
│ attribute constrains the result value itself to be well-defined (non-poison)  │
│ regardless of whether it is used along any control path. Changing to          │
│ is_zero_poison=true may produce poison for x==0, which violates noundef and   │
│ is therefore immediately UB, making the target more permissive than the       │
│ source. Alive2 reports this as Source more defined than target.               │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ - Iteration #1 adds range metadata: %ct = call noundef range(0,33)            │
│ @llvm.cttz.i32(..., false). Then InstCombine canonicalizes the icmp ne to     │
│ icmp eq (predicate swap). These are benign.                                   │
│ - Iteration #2 changes the intrinsic operand to true: %ct = call noundef      │
│ range(0,33) @llvm.cttz.i32(..., true). This is done by foldSelectCttzCtlz in  │
│ InstCombineSelect.cpp when it sees the guarding select/icmp pattern. This     │
│ modification introduces the possibility of poison when x==0 while still       │
│ keeping noundef on the call result, which is illegal.                         │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ The logic in foldSelectCttzCtlz at lines 1224–1231 only checks one-use        │
│ conditions and the current zero_is_poison flag, but it does not account for   │
│ the call's return attribute noundef. If the call result is constrained to be  │
│ non-poison (NoUndef), enabling zero_is_poison would violate that attribute    │
│ even if the result is not selected when x==0. Hence, the transformation       │
│ should be inhibited when the call has NoUndef on the return value.            │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineSelect.cpp, lines          │
│ 1224–1231.                                                                    │
│   Change the relaxation to zero_is_poison block to bail out if the cttz/ctlz  │
│ call has a NoUndef return attribute. Concretely, guard the transformation     │
│ with:                                                                         │
│     if (cast<CallBase>(II)->hasRetAttr(Attribute::NoUndef))                   │
│       return nullptr;                                                         │
│   before setting the intrinsic operand to true. The resulting block will look │
│ like:                                                                         │
│     if (II->hasOneUse() && SelectArg->hasOneUse() &&                          │
│         !match(II->getArgOperand(1), m_One())) {                              │
│       if (cast<CallBase>(II)->hasRetAttr(Attribute::NoUndef))                 │
│         return nullptr;                                                       │
│       II->setArgOperand(1, ConstantInt::getTrue(II->getContext()));           │
│     }                                                                         │
│   This prevents the creation of a poison-producing value under a noundef      │
│ constraint.                                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│   Note: IntrinsicInst derives from CallBase, so                               │
│ hasRetAttr(Attribute::NoUndef) is available. No additional includes are       │
│ necessary in this file.                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The incorrect transformation stems from foldSelectCttzCtlz relaxing to        │
│ zero_is_poison even when the cttz/ctlz call result is annotated noundef. Add  │
│ a guard to skip this relaxation if the call has NoUndef on the return. This   │
│ preserves correctness by ensuring we do not create a poison value where the   │
│ IR requires a well-defined result, and it matches the Alive2 counterexample.  │
│ The rest of the pipeline (e.g., predicate canonicalization and range          │
│ annotation) remains valid.                                                    │
